<br>
To Silly:  Yes this can affect me as I might have a slim chance at obtaining this sheild (as much of a chance as anyone) as my guild has been hunting HoT for the last month and is working on moving to the named and *hopefully* the cursed guy at the end with help from our allies.<br>
<br>
To all others.  The druid class is a versatile class, yes that is true.  That is the largest reason we are LEATHER based classes.  If you look at the three priest classes.  Druids have the most versatile abilities/spells, so they are leather, the second lowest ac armor class around.  Shamans are second to druids in the priest classes to variety in spells, that is a large reason why they are CHAIN based class, the third lowest (second highest) AC armor class.  Clerics have barley anything for versatility and that is a large reason why they get the best AC armor around for priest classes.  Of course there are other reasons, but in the encounters that I have been in in the last three months I have found that for resists, EVERYONE needs them, no class is less in need of resists then another, unless you want to do a mellee/caster(wis/int) division argument.  AoE's kill if you do not have resists, no matter who you are.  Ok, now stats (hp, mana, sta, agi, etc...), why would a cleric be more in need of a larger mana pool then a druid? so they can heal more?, well, if a druid had a larger mana pool they can dot, nuke, heal, root, ds, and do whatever they need to do more.  Each class has a job they have to do and the mana pool dictates how much they can do at one time, so why give one class a larger mana pool, higher agi, higher wisdom, higher hp, higher sta etc.. buffs then the other? (keep in note I am talking about the priest classes here not the mellee or int caster classes).<br>
<br>
Fact is, clerics get higher ac then the other two priest classes, but by giving the druids less mana/hp/stats/resists then the clerics you are just making it so the druids cannot use their variety in spells and so are a bit less usefull and who wants a less usefull druid over a higher usefull one?<br>
<br>
This is class/armor envy, I admit that, but I think I have a pretty good reason.  If I got this sheild I would be amazed just because of the time/effort/luck involved in the roll on the quest items.  So dont get me wrong, I would be exstatic if I go this sheild, I am just pointing out a common occurance that I run into with priest armor.<br>
<br>
---------<br>
