Honestly, we have many resist spells we can cast to further buff our resistances that other classes do not have available to them.  As a mater of fact, given the shields you described, a druid would still come out ahead on stats with our resist buffs on.  Perhaps that is a viable explanation for you.<br>
<br>
I imagine you are capable of obtaining the shield, I guess my real question as to why this would bother you so much, is how does it make this great shield any &quot;less&quot; great because a cleric has a better one?  I guess it's all perspective.  This is one of the best shields a druid can aquire, yet you still find fault.  I don't understand.....<br>
